snippet: Bought garlic aioli the other night and it was so spoiled that it had turned brown and runny. I thought at first from looking at the bottom it had just not been shaken enough but after removing the seal I had never been more disappointed and disgusted.

First...just not a fan of big stores like this.  But, it was clean and well stocked.  Had personnel out on floor for any questions I had.  Prices seem a bit high.  Not impressed with the layout of the grocery side.  Seems hit and miss.  They must be doing something right though...it was busy.

I love their variety and the different style and quality of clothing they offer, along with their clearance racks. Also, their variety of food, personal hygiene products and pretty much whatever you need.

I love Meijer.  They carry everything I need.  Although I went through the self check out and every register was being used the associate seen I had two beverage boxes she said I didn't have to lift them and she went and got the scanner gun.  I was impressed that I did not have to ask.  On the other hand I feel the scanner should be available to use right at the register.

My recent trip to Meijer was a delightful shopping experience from start to finish. The moment I stepped inside, I was greeted by a welcoming atmosphere that made me feel right at home. The store was impeccably clean, which not only added to the overall pleasantness but also reassured me of their commitment to hygiene and customer comfort. One thing that truly impressed me was the wide variety of products available. Meijer seems to have everything under one roof, making it incredibly convenient. From groceries to electronics, and everything in between, they had it all. Moreover, the quality of their products is outstanding. I found myself spoiled for choice with excellent options across the store. It's clear that Meijer takes pride in offering top-notch products to its customers. In summary, my visit to Meijer was a fantastic shopping experience. The combination of a welcoming atmosphere, a spotless store, an extensive product selection, and high-quality items made it a visit I'll certainly cherish and repeat.

For me, this place is a gem. Their produce department is by far the best one in Alpena. It’s  always fresh and full of stocks. They also have many varieties including Asian fruits and vegetables. Never seen a white asparagus and white/Pink strawberry before, saw them first time at this Store. Don’t forget their Sushi’s, they are delicious.

I also noticed that there’s always plenty of people who shops here. Reason? It’s CLEAN, ORGANIZED, WELL STOCKED, AMAZING STAFF EVERYWHERE, GREAT PRICES and more.

I had left a bag of groceries a week ago, they were not turned in. The service rep was wonderful and I  was able to get my groceries replaced.  They were extremely nice and very helpful. Customer service at Meijers Alpena Mich is under rated.

I always find what I need here. Except that they don't have a fabric or sewing section in this store. Everything is organized, and the store is always clean. Staff are friendly. The bottle return is better than Walmart's. They have red phones to connect to staff when a machine is down. They also provide soap, a sink, and a blow dryer to wash your hands afterwards. The interior of the bottle return is always very clean and orderly. It's located at the far side of the store by the grocery sign. It's nearby where they line all the carts up.
Great shopping experience, tons of items I have not seen on shelves, clean floors and displays, friendly associates, I got all my boats holiday meal shopping done quick and easy

Trevor, the night stocker. I asked him if he would have any habanero peppers anywhere. He took his time and looked on some pallets as he was stocking but couldn’t find any. I then told him no worries as I didn’t wanna pull him from his work or be a pain lol. He ended up finding some about 10 minutes later and found me in the store to hand them to me! Absolutely amazing and that man need a raise! Good worker, and that’s hard to find these days

They are getting just as bad as Walmart.
Online it says they have a product in store. Went to go pick it up and couldn't find it. Asked multiple employees and managers for help. All I got was excuses instead of them actually checking the back stock. Asking them to look is like pulling teeth.. when I worked retail I would have jumped to help a customer. It breaks up the boring same ol mundane work. As well as makes the customer happy. Do better Meijer...

Awful customer service. We waited almost an hour for someone in electronics, asked several employees to help us who all said that wasn't their job and to continue waiting. We even tried calling customer service several times and no answer. The employees took no responsibility and didn't care to help, even looking our way and walking away. Will not be shopping here again.
Be ready to be treated like you don’t know anything! Customer service is not good! Maybe in the morning, but not at night! Treated very poorly I recommend cracking down management!

tried my hand at the claw machine and managed to snag one but of COURSE it gets stuck. Knew I could’ve called the number and asked for a refund but REALLYYY wanted my squish. Two nice younger girls helped me the best they could and although my child is sadly still stuck dangling, I appreciate them so much for even trying and not just turning me away :’) so so sweet and the best customer service ever
The one stop grocery and general merchandise store in the state. The store is clean and well maintained. The new self checkouts work well.

Just purchased 1 lb organic carrots last night from Meijer on Hill Rd and made a salad for dinner tonight ans carrots were bad.  Not just bad, but slimy and squishy.  Disgusting.  I will be rethinking on where I go to get my groceries....Meijer is disappointing  lately.
Smaller store.  Fresh produce.  Advantages over Walmart?  The online shopping experience at Meijer isnt as advanced as Walmart.  Still a nice place to shap though.
Store was clean, well kept. Employees were helpful and knowledgable. Enjoyable shopping experienace.

This is my new Meijers store because I just moved into Alpena a week ago. I am super impressed By the size of the store And the fact that it is well stocked and very clean.  The story employees are friendly and helpful. I've now been shopping this store for about 15 months and I am still impressed with the cleanliness The fact that the shelves are well stocked with all the items that I need. I love the employees and I love to get a 44 oz diet mountain Dew from the soda fountain every time I go
I never have a bad experience when I shop at Meijer.
Very nice store. Wish we had one in Cheboygan. Our big wigs blew it.
Great store, friendly staff, pricing and clean.

Went in to find an UNO game for my grand daughters!  They had so many types of cards to choose from!  Passed the fish tanks and the clerk was so good explaning all the different types of fish. We then had to ride the pony after check out (it only cost one cent)!  It was a fun outing for all!

I and baby Rosy have visited this store and received excellent customer service and friendly personal attention from employees and customers alike!
Thank you!
The store is always clean, employees are friendly and very helpful. Prices and selection of products are great.
They should talk more Polite to their customers on rules and Regulations.
The aisles are wider than Walmart and I spend half the amount that I would have elsewhere. This store is right up there with Dollar General and Dollar tree.
Extremely helpful staff! Somewhat shocking to experience such associate to customer involvement. Very clean.

Great location with a clean layout, huge selection of local and craft beers, food from value priced to artisanal. We bought an obscene amount of groceries and our clerk Luke L. was patient, professional, and courteous. Will be back any time we visit the Alpena area!
Average meijer experience in terms of shopping, but the employees were excellent and ready/willing to help.
They let us buy turkeys this year without forcing us to buy groceries! I love Meijer
Absolutely loved this Meijer! It's sleek and modern layout is perfect. Definitely my new Alpena shopping spot!
It's great for cleanliness. Prices meh. Most of the  staff could all take lessons on customer friendliness. I will still go there until Aldi's arrives
Clean organized friendly and well cared for. Just what you expect from a Meijer.
Mobile orders are great at this store! Love this service.
Prices are ok but I can find things cheaper elsewhere usually. There fruits n veggies are more fresh and they have an eating area. I also like the fish set up.
Clean store very friendly staff and good prices
Very knowledgeable staff and always so friendly! I love this place
Found everything I was looking for one thing I have always appreciated was all the worker being helpful and professional

Said there were going to call security on us cause we can't turn in more than 25 doollers Werth of bottles at a time so they think every customer should  know this that they changed there rules that we don't know about I'm going back to Walmart ware they don't do this

We went through a fiasco with our card not working. Annabell at the service desk helped us patiently, while we were figuring out our problem. I know if I were her, I would have been irritated. Thank you for the great service!
Great selection, items Walmart doesn't carry! Homemade chocolate chip cookies, turn overs and Creme Brule creamer!  Best produce too! ❤️
On a color  tour.  Meijer  is always  a good  place  to stop  and  stretch  and a snack.  And gas.

I've always loved Meijers, but they're online experience and pick up service is is top notch! The pickup manager is always wonderful if there's ever an issue which generally there isn't. The people who bring your order to you are always friendly and take good care of your groceries. I'm so happy that they have the service and I drive over 60 mi to shop at the store because of what great people they have working there.
Has great selections a little pricey but has great deals

I live in metro Detroit this is one of the cleanest Meijer I have ever been to. Great liquor and beer selection and all the lake or camping supplies you would need in case you forget anything. Went early in the morning and it was quick in and out. Nice store!
First time here. Great selection with good prices

Nice clean store that was built less then 4 years ago. They have a good selection of produce that is typically of a higher quality then the average chain store. They also have  an adequate selection in other departments such as clothing, pet supplies, and home goods. The only departments that seemingly has a dwindling selection seems to be the outdoor sports, electronics, and camping sections albeit these are not realy the primary reason to visit this store and are more of a convince section.

Update: still the best store in the area for produce and name brand items. Have maintained a nice clean store. Only slightly negative comment is they have invested heavily in self checkout recently. I only say negative based on the fact that I don't like them

Update 2: Still a great store and while they do have a lot of self check they always do have lots of cashiers as well.

Update yet again: still a great store however the restrooms have slipped quite a bit in cleanliness.

details.update: still the best store in the area for produce and name brand items. Have maintained a nice clean store. Only slightly negative comment is they have invested heavily in self checkout recently. I only say negative based on the fact that I don't like them
details.update_2: Still a great store and while they do have a lot of self check they always do have lots of cashiers as well.
details.update_yet_again: still a great store however the restrooms have slipped quite a bit in cleanliness.

snippet: Don't like mega-stores but if its the only place to find that item....
Meijer is the only store I will I go to besides Walmart to shop for food or anything I need.
Very nice store. Well stocked and not too busy.

The service has gotten worse in the recent months. I know with the pandemic it’s hard to find workers and we are to be patient with the service. Today I just wanted to get what we needed and leave. We got home and we were missing a bag which had deodorant and shaving cream in it. We were far enough from the door that the employee could have stopped us but instead nothing. I thought they check the bag area before another customer goes through. I didn’t realize I was missing the bag until I got home. I called 3 times,the service department, so I could have them hold it but no one answered. I ended  up going back to  meijer and it wasn’t busy at all . One customer at the service desk that’s it. I went to the employee who waited on us and asked if we left a bag and she said I put it under here IN CASE you came back. How many times does this happen and people are missing items . Please Meijer do better !
Meat department rarely has sale items in stock. Always the same groceries out of stock

Meijer is a great place to shop. Lots of choices, even groceries, men's, women's and kids clothing. Only one problem, I came in to find a plain, white men's t shirt but the ones offered were stretchy, not 100% cotton, not the thicker ones I remember buying years ago. Oh well. The rest of my shopping experience went well so I'm sure I'll be back when I visit Alpena again.
We love    meijers...fresh fruit at great prices, sushi made fresh and delicious! Just a few of our family favorites ❣️ always clean and friendly

A family member has a emotional support dog and was escorted out of store on Saturday. They needed something quick from the pharmacy side of store. We are avid supporters of Meijer. We left kids to purchase what was needed. This could of been handled way differently.

Don't trust any on sale prices, I did, and I got scammed! I was asked to specify my experience, so when I see buy 2 get one free, it means you shouldn't have to pay for the 3rd item. I  don't  trust people who lie to me, so why would I trust a deceitful business?

Did an online grocery order and picked up. There were a few items they were out of but of course when the substitution was allowed it app doesn't allow you to see what they are substitute for. So eggs I had in my cart they substituted with eggs $3 more, same with water instead of one pack they did two. Atleast when Walmart does it they don't charge you the extra for items they don't have it stock. My pineapple was rotten, my hamburger was leaking all over, $35-$40 in pork spare ribs were outdated and rotten    not to mention a few other things had cracks in them and we're useless. Never again. Worst pick up ever.

They always have the items we are looking for plus great selection of fruits, vegetables and vegan food as well. Great service.
Wish we had a Meijers in Oscoda. It's a long drive but I had a doctors appointment in Alpena  -- so took advantage if shopping. I brought my cooler with ice.

I love how big of a selection Meijer has. The store is large and spacious. You can walk down isles and not be worried about those pesky isle hogs that won't move their cart, even after you've politely said 'excuse me.' The employees are usually very helpful. Bathrooms are kept clean. Great store.

This store is terrible. The employees are great people who have become victim to terrible management and corporate control.

Do yourself a favor and go to Walmart. It's the same way but at least you can carry your gun.
Higher quality items than other local big box stores
I can find everything easily.
This Meijer store is always well-stacked and organized. Cashier Jewel was very polite and efficient. Appreciate having this store near our vacation home.
The store was clean, greeted by friendly staff, got everything I wanted,  fast check out, great service. Love this place.

Trying to shop for summer clothes for my family and myself just to find out they closed there fitting rooms. How do you expect someone to try things on and buy from you. There response buy them and try them on at home and then return what I don't want. Yea NO thank you. I understand why so many racks with clearance they never sold because No one can try things on. So disappointing its past covid restrictions so don't comment back telling me this. Everyone else has there dressing rooms open...your the only one that instead of it being closed you put up walls so now it's not even there.
Aways a great experience shopping here

Everyone is so helpful. Being disabled I absolutely love shop online and pickup at store. They bring everything out and load it into my vehicle. I can shop the entire store which I could not do physically. Groceries, pet supplies, health care, even fresh fruit. Every item tells if it has mperks or another coupon. I had given up on coupons previously. Hard enough getting through the store and then messing with coupons wasn't an option. I feel great getting my shopping done and saved over $50 in coupons!
This place seems to have fresher milk and produce. Meats are good also but a little pricey. This place has it's ups and downs just like any Superstore.
At least 3 items that we wanted were on sale, and were out of stock. This seems to happen frequently.

This is a pleasantly clean and well stocked store.  But unless you buy on sale it is pricey.  The main thing I don't care for is the self check out lanes.  Every time I have used it the ladies who work that department act like you are a terrible person for bothering them for help.  One lady reeked of smoke and was antsy so I knew she needed a fix.  The regular check out lanes are usually a pretty long wait (but the clerks are nicer somehow).
That store is way too big. I wander for a long time trying to find what I'm looking for...frustrating! The way grocery products are laid out makes no sense.

Its good.love mperks. I feel like they should have more Lanes open for the holiday season! I was almost stuck in line with teenagers left alone at my house  ! (15 yo bf&gf) spent more time in line than shopping. Other than that, the store is always clean and it's never hard to find staff if I need to ask a question.

I would LOVE to give Meijer's a 5 star, but I simply can't. The staff is always helpful and they always have what I need. But after buying from the ready to go meal section and finding hair in my food I can't. This is now the second time this has happened, first time was the mini tacos and today it was the mozzarella sticks. I was told, "Well I'm not sure how it happened, everyone should ve wearing hair nets and beard nets if necessary". I don't know how hair keeps getting in the food either but I am disgusted.

An update to add, over the last year that I have been shopping here, I have seen employees was their hands for three seconds and call it good. Today I saw an employee do that and a hairnet on the floor which concerns me about the true cleanliness of the store. I am sickened by this type of behavior. After being told I would hear from a member of their care team I was informed that I would ve contacted by their store director. I missed the call and got no voicemail. It's as though they decided one call was enough and that if I didn't answer, oh well at least they tried.
The only Meijer I've been in is the Alpena one, and I've never had a bad experience.  It's always clean, and easy to shop and check out.
Very clean store employees on the floor very helpful. Cashiers could be a little bit more friendly that's the only reason you did not get five stars.

This particular location is amazing! The store itself is very nice, but what makes it shine are the staff. Every time I shop here I receive exceptional customer service. The door greeter was kind enough to explain the benefits of the mperks program and answer any questions I had, the Store Manager saw me looking around for something and stopped what he was doing to help me locate an item, even though he looked very busy, and the cashiers were very friendly and efficient. I absolutely prefer to shop here rather than "other" big box retailers in the area.
This store in Alpena is phenomenal! So clean, and well, organized! The Meijer down state where I shop, when we are at our other house, is pretty shabby . Will be back for another visit for sure!

Great place for all your grocery and household needs. Good sales if you wander around and might end up with something that wasn't on your list!! Love the pick up option! So convenient and always accurate.
Nice store..almost as nice as Walmart across the street.( They are friendlier).
Perfect northern mi meijer. Clean, organized and just overall pleasant. If you don't come here often.. it's one of those I want everything moments.
Store was well stocked. Cashier was very nice and fast. Prior Cashier from an earlier visit was horrible. Glad she wasn't there on this trip.
Typically a big fan of Meijer. This one did not have the nicest staff, even the man wearing a GM tag was rude when I asked a question about an item. It is also set up weird and the aisles are packed.

The associates were very nice & helpful. We also saved quite a lot of money.
They should get more than 5 stars!

The staff here is always friendly, the selections are great  ! Their meat department is outstanding! Always fresh, good color and always tastes great. My new favorite thing they have is their Sushi from the deli! I have never had sushi that tasted so great, and again always fresh!

Drove 20 miles into town with sky high gas prices for lightbulbs. Bought two boxes that were supposed to have three bulbs in ea. box. Drive 20 miles home to find out one box was short a bulb. Asked customer service to put a new box at the desk for my husband to exchange the next morning, and to save me another 20 minutes both ways trip again. They would not do it. There was ZERO customer service for this issue. I got a crisp apology and a sob story about their “rules” rather than SERVICE. Also, I spent 400.00 that day in the alpena Mi store. $400.00, and ZERO customer service. Disgusting. I’ll be returning both packages of lightbulbs now, and I Will be reconsidering where I spend my large wads of cash for groceries and housewares.

Love the store, but the cashier's need to be retrained on how to properly bag items. I've had things crushed and have had raw meat put in with produce and cleaning chemicals put in with food items every time I've gone in there. I've also asked them to put frozen items in the freezer bags I take with me and have been ignored so I'm constantly rebagging my items myself after being checked out. If they fix this issue this will be a great place to shop.
Great Meijer store. Produce selections are fresh & abundant with an array of unique fruits & veggies. Very clean, well stocked

Been shopping at Meijer since they opened here.  Over the course of the last year or so, I've really had to look at my receipts very closely.  Can't do it when you are being checked out,  but when I get home, that is the first thing I do.  It seems to be happening more and more.  This week alone I have had to return to the store twice to get discounts that should have been included to begin with.  $15.00 in these 2 transactions alone!!!  I like their store, but feel like I'm being taken advantage of.  BTW...my $10 item was listed as bogo free, and wasn't even in their registers!
High quality shopping experience.

The general manager of the store doesn't really care for his customers they tend to believe their employees before they believe the customer we had a messed up cake and  He believed the Baker not over the customer and it did not have whipped is whipped icing it was butter icing when we had it for our 7 year old son's birthday it was incorrect I would recommend to anybody Never order a cake from here they don't care it's all about them it's not about you

I always have a good experience here, the people are friendly and the store is amazingly clean for our area. The only problem I have is the grocery layout is kind of odd. I sometimes have a problem finding what I need, but the employees are always very helpful and nice. I never feel like I'm bothering them, especially the electronics group. Very knowledgeable and helpful staff.
Absolutely love this new store. Staff is awesome and produce is wonderful. Will be my new store to shop.

I was not very happy with my last visit.  I was looking for some powder, I stopped an employee to ask her where it might be, all I got was it could be down there or down there and she walked off, didn't help me look for it or find someone that could.  I go to the other end of the store, stop at a aisle to let an employee with carts go through, no thank you, acknowledgement at all. Go to the bread aisle, there was an employee checking the bread, I ask him jokingly which loaf is the softness, he didn't even look my  way at all.  Very rude people in that store.  Think I will start shopping at Walmart.

The store is always clean, but I can never ever find an employee to help me and when I do they pass the buck. So sad for them...that is how one learns. Sometimes I swear they have radar and know you are headed to ask them for help so they take off never to be seen again. Plus they notify all their co-workers.
I get more help from customers than employees...maybe they ought to cut some hourly pay or mgrs pay for not paying attention to the employees performance.
The manager Linda was especially helpful in regards to an issue I had that was not resolved correctly until she stepped in. But I generally enjoy shopping at Meijer
It’s asinine that Meijer would have a clothing department with no fitting rooms. Either get rid of the clothing department or bring back the fitting rooms.

Went to self serve checkout because only one line was open with a cashier. The self checkout kept telling me there was something in the bag not accounted for and to wait for assistance. After waiting about three or four minutes with no employee in site to offer assistance I left the checkout and stood in line at the one register line open for another 15 minutes to checkout. No one was present at self serve checkouts and it was very frustrating.
Your truly selection is remarkable and it made me moist with excitement

Crazy good service! Guy from seafood wasn't busy so I asked him about pine nuts I couldn't find. He combed the store for me. 20 minutes later, while I was in line at register, he shows up with the pine nuts! I couldn't believe it. Best service ever!!!

Best service, amazing staff. I was talking to my friend about cutlery and the associate overheard me so he guided me to where it was. I can't believe how friendly the staff was. I wish more stores were like this.
Great place!  Stay away from Wally World
I love the ease of the shop and scan option for whenever I actually go in person. I love the pick up option as well, just wish they'd deliver to my house. It's really not far!

I wish I could shop here more often but the closest store is 50+ miles away now that I live in northern Mi.
The garbage on the edge of their parking lot is disgusting!! I hope they read this and clean up after their local customers.

Expansive, clean store with lots of choices. If you're used to Walmart however not good prices. I had a couple donuts and then did find one bargain--my beloved Steel Reserve $1.59 8.1% 24 oz cans of beer were on sale for a $1.09 --hey, stock up for summer!

I like the cooked food their at the store is convenient for ppl that’s hungry at a low price

And their food selection is good

Always check out the deals on meats at the Meijers store.
They have very good meats and won't buy any beaf from Walmart because it is all prepackaged and Meijers is always fresh cut.
Great store but you have to buy two items to get 1/2 on third items

Love that store. They had what I needed after going 3 other places first but thought I would just see if they carried patriot jersey and items for a young man and they did. Then to my surprise all three items were cheaper than I thought.  Great day at Meijers.
Store was clean. Registers were actually manned by humans. Check out was acceptably timely.

I love Meijer. So much space to shop. You can fit 3-4 carts down each row no problem. You can stop and look at things without anyone rushing you. Its clean. The produce is awesome. And the workers are not disgruntled. I'll always shop meijer.

Amazing selection of quality products. Yes, some things can be more expensive, what compared to other stores like Walmart... the quality beats the price. Very friendly staff and the store is almost always clean and well-stocked I never have a problem finding anything I need. If you're looking to eat healthy or to have better and higher-quality food this is your choice of store.
The price difference on most items is because almost everything is locally sourced. These items aren't being shipped from China you don't have tomatoes that are being shipped halfway across the country - everything is growing as close as possible to stay as fresh as possible.
A clean store that carries everything you'd expect from a Meijer's.

Great place for groceries,  produce is fresh, deli/bakery is Amazing. Lots of dairy selections, alot of general merch to find just what you're actually looking for! Staff are very friendly and respectful, 100% 5 star rating.
Very pleasant friendly people

I really found this Meier's worth an hour's drive to get my gluten free foods. They were very well stocked with many varieties of gf foods.
I found they had a large selection of meats and other household needs. The prices were also worth the trip.

Too expensive. Expansive have to go all over the store to find what you need. Minimal staff. Bought canned items as well as soup starters that were already expired. Who would think one would have to check dates on those products. Can get most everything less expensive elsewhere especially staples and clothing. It seems that even clearance is higher than one would expect to pay. Quality is generally ok.
There should be a general store map to help save time and energy so someone could stop on lunch hour run in and out. Checking out is a nightmare
Everyone is very courteous,and helpful!!!! ✌️  %
Clean, well stocked and the people are super friendly.
Floors are made of better concrete than Walmart's. They are a bit easier to walk on. Basic items seem to have a 50/50 chance of being out of stock.
Nice shopping store, has just about everything you would need... clothes, food, drink.
Got what I was looking for fairly quickly. Didn't need help finding it & was able to check out with only a short wait; only 1 person in front of me.

Great selection. They would not accept my Minnesota license when I tried to buy beer, however. Claimed I had a fake. I do not have a fake and I suspect they lack proper training in recognizing other states' licenses.

Edit: they've figured it out and I have successfully bought beer!

details.edit: they've figured it out and I have successfully bought beer!

response.snippet: Sam, thank you for bringing this experience to our attention. We'd like to apologize for having your ID denied, and please know we will be sharing this with the rest of the team.  If you’d like to connect directly on this, please contact us at bit.ly/MeijerHelp

snippet: Stopped by to get fuel, the coffee machine dispensed only hot water,. Apparently this is a known issue that has been going on for some time. So the clerk did go to the machine and slapped it in the side so it would drop the instant coffee powder..... Needless to say, not impressed... The coffee we paid for was horrible.... Now what I am about to suggest is very radical.... How about fix the machine using something called parts! Very disappointed with Meijer.

Ive always loved Meijer! I was raised in Greenville MI where the first Meijer was established. A lot of respect! However this Meijer has it's good and bad. First of all some nice employees are hard to find unless it's a cashier. The fellas there are awkwardly avoidant of assisting people as they walked by. I must have stood in front of the fish tanks with obvious interest of wanting to buy some. Waited a dang half hour.. maybe longer. More than several employees looked me and intentionally diverted direction towards me. The ones even walking straight at me!... Literally they took sharp turns to avoid me and continued towards electronics. They were even in the same isle as me as they walked four isles out of their way to there. Similar issue to buying a tv. I asked the fella after he returned from the back room as I stood and waited looking in his direction expecting help. Finally I got his attention by letting him know I'm interested in one.. He got a ride bit grumpy with his tone.. I asked him if I could just carry it up because it wasn't too heavy for me. I've never bought one there before.. he simply replied "It's my job to provide customer service..." Probably the most miserable tone I've heard come out of retail. I said "Okay, right.. I just want to know how to go about this, I'd hate to distrub anyone."
His reply was as simple as "No... I'll haul it up in a cart.... Ask your cashier when you ring up." I waited there for a few moments for him to cart it up, he wheels it to the customer service desk. So I stand in line to buy the rest of my stuff. Told the cashier that I have a TV to buy.. she says "Okay..." And just looks at me and slow blinks. I was confused at this point, so I pointed at the TV and told her I was told to bring it up to her so I can buy it. So then she shruggs her shoulders at me and tells me to go to customer service to buy it. I walk over to customer service and I said I'd like to buy that TV and pointed at it. She says "alright" and stares at me signaling some explanation. I let her know that a cashier sent me over and she was absolutely confused! Nice though (finally) and she helped me out.
